    <thetext>Its harder to (In reply to comment #0)
&gt; Bibletime UI (as all other modern UI) should be able to auto-detect the
&gt; system&apos;s language and, if the language is available, activate it automatically
&gt; (whitout the user needing to get the file from the website m-a-n-u-a-l-l-y! :(

As far as I know, BibleTime should auto-detect the language. Could you please comment a bit on how you currently manually change the language?

&gt; There should also be a place to manually change the UI language.

I guess we could implement such a feature right away, but if we do it now it would still need that BibleTime be restarted for the change to apply.

&gt; (really... how can such a great front end miss something so basic?! Not
&gt; everyone is a computer expert)

For more than a year we&apos;ve been working towards a solution which would make it able to change the language of BibleTime at runtime. In reality, this is a lot harder to implement than it might seem. But eventually, we&apos;ll be able to change the language of the application at runtime.</thetext>
