    <thetext>(sorry. copy/past gone wrong - my fault... here&apos;s the complete reply)


&gt; As far as I know, BibleTime should auto-detect the language. Could you please
&gt; comment a bit on how you currently manually change the language?

Well, that&apos;s the thing... I don&apos;t change it! :( 
I just assumed that it could be changed, since you do have the language files available for download!

I&apos;m Portuguese and i&apos;ve even started the translation of BibleTime into Pt-Pt... however, since i didn&apos;t saw any way to change the language, i stopped. I thought that in the absense of the pt-pt language file, it would fall into pt-br or allow a user to select the prefered language!

But now, from what you&apos;re saying, i&apos;m starting to think that BibleTime works fine and, because it does not have a pt-pt, it does fall into english language... is that it?

if that&apos;s the problem, next week i&apos;ll get you a pt-pt UI file translated!


&gt; I guess we could implement such a feature right away, but if we do it now it
&gt; would still need that BibleTime be restarted for the change to apply.

I think everyone would be Ok whit that! Just an Alert saying that BibleTime would have to be restarted would work just fine! I thing having such an option (even if we have to restart BT to get the new language) makes total sense!!! e.g.: I&apos;m portuguese, there&apos;s no pt-pt language, but most portuguese users would understand much better pt-br that en.

e.g.2: I now a lot of people from other countries. They buy portables here in portugal - the Operating system cames in Portuguese, but those people could prefere to choose their own language which they understand better

More options = better software ;)

I guess that (very sadly) is a litle late to get it into 2.9 (since it&apos;s on RC2 already) but please, do add that option ASAP!

I&apos;ll get you that pt-pt file next week!</thetext>
