Hi,

yes there is an unification already ruling! However there will remain a few words (very few, indeed!) that will remain different. 
The major problem, however, is not those few words but the approach to the text chosen. To give you a simple and quick example (of many)in english (on the applications menu&apos;s) we find the &quot;File&quot; word. The problem is that in Portugal that word is directly translated from english and we get &quot;Ficheiro&quot;, but in Brazil they use &quot;Arquivo&quot; (&quot;archive&quot;, in english!) and no matter what you do, neither country will change this (even when we know that &quot;Arquivo&quot; and &quot;Ficheiro&quot; are two words that exist in both countries).

so, as you can see from the above example, there will have to be Pt and Pt_Br translations files for years to came :(




Now... other subject: i&apos;ve completed the BT translations into Pt-Pt!!! ;) where do i send it? can you give me an e-mail address or something like that?


Tks</thetext>
